    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "This project aims to curate a comprehensive collection of films and interviews featuring one of Cuba’s most influential filmmakers of the 21st century. Within this archive, you will have access to a series of interviews conducted over the years, as well as a freely available selection of his filmography. The objective is to provide a resource that deepens the understanding of his contributions to cinema, both as an innovative filmmaker and an individual."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "url": "https://habanerofilmsales.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/bahia-otherangle.jpeg",
      "caption": "Shot from Fábula (2011)",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Directions:",
          "bold": true,
          "italic": true,
          "underline": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "italic": true,
          "underline": true,
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "- First, read the introduction page title \"Introducing Lester Hamlet: A Pivotal Figure in Contemporary Cuban Cinema\""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "- Secondly, watch both of Lester Hamlet’s available films, "
        },
        {
          "text": "Casa Vieja",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "text": "Tres Veces Dos",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": "."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "- Thirdly, watch the recent interview with Jack Riordan, while following along with the annotations to complement the interview."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Extra Material (Optional):"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "- Lester's Relationship with his Father (Trauma + Exile), watch other curated interviews such as the interviews with: Amaury Pérez, Yadira Otero, or Marco en Marcos. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "horizontal-separator",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Lester Hamlet’s debut film, "
        },
        {
          "text": "Tres Veces Dos",
          "italic": true
        },
        {
          "text": ", is a full-length feature that showcases three short films by emerging Cuban filmmakers of the early 2000s: Pavel Giroud, Lester Hamlet, and Esteban Insausti. Each of these directors would later achieve national and international recognition, becoming award-winning filmmakers celebrated around the world."
        }
      ]
